folder: Kings Highway & Snyder Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
King's Highway, (rear view) between Snyder (right) and Tilden Aves., looking westward. On the east side of King's Highway, from left to right, are the homes of P. Remsen (1873) and T.S. Remsen (1860-1873); between them in the background are Nos. 280-282 East 56th Street. To the left of the P. Remsen house, is a 2 1/2 story house; which is No. 316 East 56th Street.

1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Snyder Avenue

folder: Kings Highway & Snyder Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1) King's Highway, east side, between Snyder and Tilden Aves., showing the Schenck Remsen house (1860-1873), which was occupied by Jacob D. Remsen in 1903. It is still standing in 1929.

March 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same.

May 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same, a front view.

March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4) The same, viewed across King's Highway. It was the property of Cornelius Kouwenhoven in 1923.

September 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Assuming Street to be North and South.
